s ","position":{"start":{"line":15,"column":1},"end":{"line":15,"column":1}},"key":"EjYnocaLtU"},{"type":"emphasis","position":{"start":{"line":15,"column":1},"end":{"line":15,"column":1}},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"The Turing Way","position":{"start":{"line":15,"column":1},"end":{"line":15,"column":1}},"key":"uEx2WfhY0H"}],"key":"YKsdikTxSm"},{"type":"text","value":" Community and then authors are listed in alphabetical order by last name.\nAuthorship is cumulative so authors will always remain authors.\nConsequently, this model of authorship gives equal recognition as an author to any contribution and therefore in this sense is an authorship of contributors rather than authors.","position":{"start":{"line":15,"column":1},"end":{"line":15,"column":1}},"key":"lJSsTDhVBS"}],"key":"xyEOlZeuE4"},{"type":"paragraph","position":{"start":{"line":20,"column":1},"end":{"line":21,"column":1}},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"This is similar to a consortia authorship.\nThis is a collective of authors and all members of the consortium are considered authors and must be listed in the published articles as such. Sometimes this is seen in the journal as a large list of authors or can be shown as the community name, however underneath all of the author names of the community will be visible.","position":{"start":{"line":20,"column":1},"end":{"line":20,"column":1}},"key":"qiRgSzIpFF"}],"key":"NZbt3PhXGR"},{"type":"paragraph","position":{"start":{"line":23,"column":1},"end":{"line":25,"column":1}},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"Another recent development in the use of the CRediT taxonomy is the idea of providing a cover page to an article much like seen on film-credits. This recent ","position":{"start":{"line":23,"column":1},"end":{"line":23,"column":1}},"key":"shTEIpnjb1"},{"type":"link","url":"https://livingwithmachines.ac.uk/highlighting-authors-contributions-and-interdisciplinary-collaborations-in-living-with-machines/","position":{"start":{"line":23,"column":1